HEADWORD: Treckschuyt
<hw>Treck"schuyt`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>trekschuit</ets>; <ets>trekken</ets> to draw + <ets>schuit</ets> a
boat. Cf. <er>Trackscout</er>.]</ety> <def>A covered boat for goods and
passengers, used on the Dutch and Flemish canals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

